en associated since the mid-1970s, Hejinian turns to language as a social space, a site of both philosophical inquiry and political address.Central to these essays are the themes of time and knowledge, consciousness and perception. Hejinian's interests cover a range of texts and figures. Prominent among them are Sir Francis Bacon and Enlightenment-era explorers; Faust and Sheherazade; Viktor Shklovsky and Russian formalism; William James, Hannah Arendt, and Martin Heidegger. But perhaps the most important literary presence in the essays is Gertrude Stein; the volume includes Hejinian's influential "Two Stein Talks," as well as two more recent essays on Stein's writings.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPoetics. 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  aacademic.  aamerican literature.  aamerican poetry.  aamerican poets.  aautobiographical.  acollected works.  aconsciousness.  acontemporary poetry.  acreative writing.  aenlightenment.  aessay collection.  afaust.  afemale poets.  agertrude stein.  aknowledge.  alanguage poets.  aliterary analysis.  aliterary criticism.  aliterary culture.  amartin heidegger.  amodern poetry.  aperception.  aphilosophy.  apoetry.  apolitical.  apolitics.  ascheherazade.  ascholarly.  asir francis bacon.  atime.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052021700340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092227340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520922273423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520922273/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY